{{Quote|After writing for a circus, a university, and co-writing sport autobiographies I realized that while I loved writing, I desperately wanted to tell my own stories. The first step in that direction was LucasFilm. They hired me to create a middle grade trilogy featuring Anakin Solo (the youngest son of Han and Leia in the adult novels). It was a joy to imagine Anakin's adventures at a Jedi Academy! I'm a HUGE Star Wars and science fiction fan so being part of the Star Wars world was incredible and it gave me the courage to begin writing my own stories.|Nancy Richardson Fischer|<ref name="Q&A" />}}
'''Nancy Richardson Fischer'''<ref name="Q&A" /> is the author of the first three books of the ''[[Star Wars: Junior Jedi Knights]]'' series, which she wrote under the name '''Nancy Richardson'''.<ref name="The Golden Globe">''[[Junior Jedi Knights: The Golden Globe]]''</ref><ref name="Lyric's World">''[[Junior Jedi Knights: Lyric's World]]''</ref><ref name="Promises">''[[Junior Jedi Knights: Promises]]''</ref> She has also been credited as '''Nancy Ann Richardson'''<ref name="Fantastic Fiction">{{WebCite|url=https://www.fantasticfiction.com/r/nancy-ann-richardson/|title=Nancy Ann Richardson|work=Fantastic Fiction|archivedate=20240415143806}}</ref> and '''Nan Fischer'''.<ref name="Official Site">{{OfficialSite|url=https://nanfischerauthor.com/|text=Nanfischerauthor.com|archivedate=20250205192434}}</ref>

After graduation from [[Wikipedia:Cornell University|Cornell University]], a young Nancy Richardson was hired as a staff writer for the [[Wikipedia:Ringling Bros. and Barnum & Bailey Circus|Ringling Bros. and Barnum & Bailey Circus]], which led to her realizing she could potentially make a living as a writer. Her earliest books were sports autobiographies for athletes such as [[Wikipedia:Monica Seles|Monica Seles]] and [[Wikipedia:Apolo Ohno|Apolo Ohno]]. She credits [[Lucasfilm]] hiring her to write a trilogy of middle-grade novels starring [[Anakin Solo]] as the first step toward her getting the courage to be able to write her own stories.<ref name="Q&A" /> Although she afterward hit what she calls a "drought," she kept writing and eventually saw her own original novels start to get published.<ref name="Trans Media Mutts">{{WebCite|url=https://www.transmediamutts.com/blog/nancy-richardson-fischer-author-of-when/|text=Nancy Richardson Fischer, author of WHEN ELEPHANTS FLY, on it taking a village to produce a book|work=Trans Media Mutts|author=Jocelyn Rish|archiveurl=https://archive.md/jwO5A}}</ref>

